{
  "title": "Cmake->How do I use a different compiler?",
  "cells": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "data": "<embed id=\"xunlei_com_thunder_helper_plugin_d462f475-c18e-46be-bd10-327458d045bd\" type=\"application/thunder_download_plugin\" height=\"0\" width=\"0\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px;\"><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 15px auto 2px; padding: 0px; font-size: 16px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span id=\"How_do_I_use_a_different_compiler.3F\" class=\"mw-headline\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">How do I use a different compiler?</span></h3><h4 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; margin: 15px auto 2px; padding: 0px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span id=\"Method_1:_use_environment_variables\" class=\"mw-headline\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Method 1: use environment variables</span></h4><p style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; margin: 10px auto; padding: 0px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;\">For C and C++, set the&nbsp;<tt style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">CC</tt>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<tt style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">CXX</tt>&nbsp;environment variables. This method is not guaranteed to work for all generators. (Specifically, if you are trying to set Xcode's&nbsp;<tt style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">GCC_VERSION</tt>, this method confuses Xcode.)</p><p style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; margin: 10px auto; padding: 0px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;\">For example:</p><pre style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 20px;\">CC=gcc-4.2 CXX=/usr/bin/g++-4.2 cmake -G \"Your Generator\" path/to/your/source\n</pre><h4 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; margin: 15px auto 2px; padding: 0px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span id=\"Method_2:_use_cmake_-D\" class=\"mw-headline\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Method 2: use cmake -D</span></h4><p style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; margin: 10px auto; padding: 0px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;\">Set the appropriate&nbsp;<tt style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">CMAKE_FOO_COMPILER</tt>&nbsp;variable(s) to a valid compiler name or full path on the command-line using&nbsp;<tt style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">cmake -D</tt>.</p><p style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; margin: 10px auto; padding: 0px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;\">For example:</p><pre style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 20px;\">cmake -G \"Your Generator\" -D CMAKE_C_COMPILER=gcc-4.2 -D CMAKE_CXX_COMPILER=g++-4.2 path/to/your/source\n</pre><h4 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; margin: 15px auto 2px; padding: 0px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span id=\"Method_3_.28avoid.29:_use_set.28.29\" class=\"mw-headline\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Method 3 (avoid): use set()</span></h4><p style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; margin: 10px auto; padding: 0px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;\">Set the appropriate&nbsp;<tt style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">CMAKE_FOO_COMPILER</tt>&nbsp;variable(s) to a valid compiler name or full path in a list file using&nbsp;<tt style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">set()</tt>. This must be done&nbsp;<em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">before</em>&nbsp;any language is set (ie before any&nbsp;<tt style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">project()</tt>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<tt style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">enable_language()</tt>&nbsp;command).</p><p style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; margin: 10px auto; padding: 0px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;\">For example:</p><pre style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 20px;\">set(CMAKE_C_COMPILER \"gcc-4.2\")\nset(CMAKE_CXX_COMPILER \"/usr/bin/g++-4.2\")\n\nproject(\"YourProjectName\")</pre>"
    }
  ]
}